There was a [PR](https://github.com/kubernetes/release/pull/386) to update this repository's `kubeadm.conf` to match the copy used by bazel builds in the [kubernetes repo](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/898b1b333068430edfa29b6f7b17dbab458c1846/build/debs/kubeadm-10.conf). Unfortunately, this commit needed to be rolled back because its changes should only apply to Kubernetes versions >= 1.8, and a release of 1.7.3 erroneously included the change.

Since the `release` repository doesn't follow the same branching scheme as the main `kubernetes` repository, this logic might need to live in the [debian](https://github.com/kubernetes/release/blob/17849e6a6c6f206a68f1a33e6c2e7d71bee6564a/debian/build.go)/[rpm](https://github.com/kubernetes/release/blob/17849e6a6c6f206a68f1a33e6c2e7d71bee6564a/rpm/docker-build.sh) builders.

